[In 2016, after a massive, decades-long vaccination campaign, WHO declared Latin America free of measles. But less than 2 years later, a virulent outbreak in Venezuela, combined with a mass exodus from the country, is threatening that medical success story. Brazil and Colombia have reported cases of measles, all imported from Venezuela. Peru now also has reported a case -- see next post. This is clear evidence why vaccination must be maintained even in countries that are declared "measles-free", and it is further evidence of the global world in which we live where borders are political designations and do not prevent spread of pathogens. - Mod.LK]

