[5] South America (Peru, Lima ex Venezuela), imported case, health alert
Date: Fri 13 Jul 2018
Source: Garda World [edited]
https://elcomercio.pe/peru/declaran-alerta-epidemiologica-pais-caso-sarampion-noticia-535252
English: https://www.garda.com/crisis24/news-alerts/135636/peru-health-officials-warn-of-possible-measles-outbreak-in-lima


According to health officials, at least one imported case of measles was confirmed in Lima [Peru] as of early July [2018]. Local sources report that the patient, a one year old child, contracted the disease in Venezuela. Health officials have issued an epidemiological alert and implemented public health measures, including vaccination campaigns, to limit further spread of the disease.

Potentially affected individuals are advised to ensure their measles vaccination is up to date (including booster shots) and to contact their doctor with any questions or concerns. Anyone experiencing symptoms [high fever, runny nose, cough, red and watery eyes, small white spots inside the cheeks, and rash spreading from the face and neck to the hands and feet over several days] is urged to seek immediate medical attention.

