[6] USA (Oregon)
Date: Tue 17 Jul 2018
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/measles-3rd-person-confirmed-multnomah-county-oregon-53042/


In a follow-up to recent measles cases in Multnomah County, Oregon, health officials have confirmed that a 3rd person with measles symptoms has tested positive for the virus. The 3rd individual in Multnomah County tested positive for measles 13 Jul 2018. This person was unvaccinated and had been in close contact with a 2nd individual diagnosed with measles on 6 Jul 2018.

Multnomah County Communicable Disease Services had alerted this 3rd individual of the exposure and asked the person to stay at home and away from others. The 3rd individual was in daily contact with Multnomah County's team to check for symptoms.

"Once again our measles response plan worked, thanks to another individual willing to stay away from others and call us at the first sign of symptoms," said Multnomah County deputy health officer, Dr Jennifer Vines.

The 1st case in Multnomah County was confirmed in the Portland metro area -- the 1st since 2014. The 1st individual did have vaccine records. A person who spent time with the 1st individual during the infectious period did not have documentation of prior immunizations. That person tested positive for measles 6 Jul 2018 and has remained home. However, that 2nd individual had been in daily contact with a 3rd individual who also did not have records of prior immunization. That person tested positive for measles Fri 13 Jul 2018.

