[7] Uganda
Date: Mon 16 Jul 2018
Source: The Observer [edited]
https://observer.ug/news/headlines/58191-gov-t-confirms-measles-outbreak-in-ntoroko-mayuge.html


The government has confirmed a measles outbreak in Ntoroko and Mayuge districts. Dr Josephine Bwago, the department head of the Expanded Programme on Immunisation (EPI) at the Uganda Virus Research Institute, says they received specimens from 6 suspected measles cases from Mayuge district on 11 Jul 2018 and another 7 from Ntoroko district on 12 Jul 2018.

Dr Bwago says all the specimens tested positive for measles. All the cases from Ntoroko are from Kanara subcounty, while those from Mayuge are from Baitambogwe, Mpungwe and Wairasa subcounties. According to the laboratory results report, all cases are aged between 2 and 4 months.

In May [2018], the government announced an outbreak of measles in 26 districts across the country. The most affected then included Amuru, Kamuli, Mbale and Butebo districts.

[byline: URN]

